- The addition point for graph-owned reserved op families is src/sdk/video/timeline/patch.ts: (a) extend TimelinePatchReservedOpFamily type (lines 34-36) with 'graph.node.add' | 'graph.node.update' | 'graph.node.remove' | 'graph.node.move' | 'graph.edge.add' | 'graph.edge.update' | 'graph.edge.remove' | 'graph.group.add' | 'graph.group.update' | 'graph.group.remove'; (b) extend TIMELINE_PATCH_RESERVED_OP_FAMILIES array (lines 62-65) with matching string literals; (c) the combined TIMELINE_PATCH_ALL_OP_FAMILIES auto-includes them via spread at line 69-72.
- For graph diff granularities, the addition point is also src/sdk/video/timeline/patch.ts: extend TimelineDiffGranularity type (lines 138-143) with 'graph' | 'node' | 'edge' (or 'graph-node' | 'graph-edge' if scoped naming is preferred) and mirror in TIMELINE_DIFF_GRANULARITIES array (lines 146-152). The granularity type is not gated through reserved/active — it serves as a label on diff entries and carries no execution semantics, so adding graph granularities does not require validation changes.
- Downstream consumers of the reserved vocabulary that will automatically recognize new entries: (a) src/sdk/index.ts lines 123-124 — barrel exports of both the type and const; (b) src/tools/video-editor/lib/timeline-patch.ts — RESERVED_OPS set, validateTimelinePatch, compileTimelinePatch, previewTimelinePatch; (c) src/sdk/__tests__/sdk-boundary.test.ts line 126 — imports TimelinePatchReservedOpFamily type for boundary type-check tests; (d) src/examples/command-extension.ts line 50 and src/examples/surface-coverage.ts line 38 — example consumers importing the type/const.
